article.headline: UNLV 69, Murray St. 55
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. -- Chace Stanback scored 19 points to lead UNLV to a 69-55 victory over Murray State in the 76 Classic on Friday night. Quintrell Thomas added 12 points, six rebounds and two blocks for the Rebels (5-0), who will play Virginia Tech for the championship on Sunday. Oscar Bellefield had 10 points and six assists. Isacc Miles and Isaiah Canaan each scored 11 points for the Racers (3-2). B.J. Jenkins added eight points, six rebounds and two assists. Despite a season-low point total, UNLV shot a season-best 58.7 percent and scored 21 points off 16 turnovers.
